The publication of the book 'Diario de un Poeta recién Casado' includes the triennium 
The presentation of the first illustrated edition of "Diario de un Poeta recién Casado 'in the St Stephen's Church (New York) - a place where Juan Ramón Jiménez married 1916 Zenobia offers an appropriate atmosphere, carrying out planned activities on behalf of the Andalusian Council for Culture, to celebrate the' triennium of Zenobia and Juan Ramón" (2008). The goal is the commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the award of the Nobel Prize for literature and the death of the two. 
